{{#if (eq template "nextjs")}}
## Next.js Specifics

- **Always** use the App Router. Never suggest `pages/` directory patterns.
- Server Components are the default; `"use client"` is opt-in.
- Mutations go in Server Actions, not client-side fetch calls.
- Use `next/image` for all `<img>` tags.
- Keep environment secrets out of `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix.
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq template "api")}}
## API Specifics

- HTTP layer (routes) must not contain business logic — delegate to services.
- Zod schemas are the single source of truth for input shapes.
- Response envelope: `{ data: T | null, error: string | null, meta?: object }`.
- Log errors server-side; return user-safe messages to clients.
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq template "cli")}}
## CLI Specifics

- Parse arguments with Commander; interactive prompts with `@inquirer/prompts`.
- All options must have `.description()` for `--help`.
- Use `process.exitCode = 1` over `process.exit(1)` where possible (allows cleanup).
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq template "react")}}
## React Specifics

- Data fetching: TanStack Query (never raw `useEffect` + `fetch`).
- Routing: React Router v6 with `createBrowserRouter`.
- Styling: Tailwind utility classes; no inline styles.
- State: local → `useState`, global → Zustand, server → TanStack Query.
{{/if}}

## Hard Rules

- Never commit `.env` — the committed file is always `.env.example`.
- No `any` in TypeScript — zero tolerance.
- Conventional commits only: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`.
- No speculative or "nice to have" features unless explicitly requested.
